# Svelte 5 Patterns

## Runes

- `$state()` for reactive state (not implicit `let`)
- `$derived()` for computed values (not `$:`)
- `$effect()` for side effects (not `$:`)
- `$props()` for component props (not `export let`)
- `$bindable()` for two-way binding

## Snippets

- Use `{#snippet}` and `{@render}` instead of `<slot>` for composition

## Shared Logic

- Extract reusable reactive logic to `.svelte.ts` or `.svelte.js` files

## SvelteKit

- Prefer Remote Functions (`$app/server`) over manual API routes for type-safe client-server calls
- Use `$app/environment` (`browser`, `building`, `dev`) for environment checks
- Use `$app/navigation` for `goto`, `invalidate`, shallow routing, etc.

## Styling (this repo)

- Prefer shared tokens and globals in `src/app.css`; use component `<style>` for scoped layout or one-off rules
- Keep color/contrast logic consistent with the project’s semantic color approach (see existing `src` patterns)
